⬇️⬇️ Links, schedule, and more information down below! ⬇️⬇️

Welcome! Come join for some motivation and accountability! Here we follow the 50/10 Pomodoro method, where we work for 50 minutes and then take a 10 minute break to chat, relax, craft and play puzzles! (we're obsessed with jumble words...)

I am a physics PhD student in my second year at the University of Auckland. My PhD is purely theoretical and computational, so I do lots of coding. My research looks at gravitational wave physics in relation to supermassive black holes and the future Laser Interferometer Space Antenna.

I did my undergraduate and masters in the UK, where I grew up, and then moved to New Zealand for my PhD. I now do purely research and don't take any classes, but I do teach some!

S4.description:
📩open me:

Hi!
Welcome to another Study with me
Thanks for joining
_________________________

I hope this study video helps you avoid using social media while you study. You will find a quiet and cosy study room ambience in this video when studying at your home. Hopefully, this would get you motivated more for studying. You might hear the rain, birds, typing sounds and the flipping of pages (and cars too, unfortunately) from time to time, and I hope that helps you know that I'm there studying with you!

🔥Key to success - """"BE CONSISTENT""""🔥

___________________________

What are you studying and where are you joining from? I also wonder what type of videos you like, study at the library or study at home? Your opinions are quite important to me; and, if you let me know what type of videos you like to watch, I would be happy. 
_____________________________

✧･ﾟ at the beginning of the study sessions, make sure to:
- turn off anything you're not going to be using to study
- have your materials ready to go
- have drinks/food ready so you don't have to get up to go get necessities
- have a clear idea of what you want to accomplish during the session (i.e., choose a task from your to-do list)


✧･ﾟ during the breaks:
- stop working as soon as the timer hits, even if you're mid-sentence
- make sure to get up, do some simple stretches
- refill anything that needs to get refilled
- talk to friends/update family

✧･ﾟ at the end of this video:
if you want to continue studying, give yourself a longer break and you can the next session video!

you're set to go! ♡
_____________________________
💡Please adjust the volume for each of the background music that comes out.
The ASMR that comes out with 💡 is the sound of burning wood and Rain. 
_____________________________

We have a Chat bot- 🤖
Commands for chat bot- 

!hi - when you join in👋
!start - to start studying
!top - Top Points
!points -  to know your points💯
!complete - when done with the goal

Chat rules:
- Being nice and respectful is mandatory!
- Spamming, harassment, trolling, bullying, repeating and all capital messages are definitely prohibited!
- Please feel encouraged to write in English so no one would feel excluded in the chat :)
- Please check YouTube's Community Guidelines
_____________________________

To those who are starting :
In order to study or do anything for long periods of time you need a strong purpose and you must be willing to endure challenges. If I can do this, think about what you can accomplish. If you're starting out, start from low intervals(10-30 minutes) and gradually increase once you feel you're comfortable. If you feel like quitting, visualize your goals and evaluate your purpose. Learn to accept challenges in your life to become uncommon.

JUST DO IT!

안녕하세요! 법무사 시험을 준비하는 꾸준맨 부맨입니다.
이전에는 장교(ROTC 출신)로 해병대에 6년간 몸담았고, 전역 후 그간 배워보고 싶었던 영상 편집, 코딩, IT(네트워크, 정보보안 등) 여러가지를 공부 했습니다. 그러던 중 좋은 기회를 만나 쿠팡 자회사인 CFS에 입사. 물류센터에서 근무를 했습니다. 군인시절부터 조직(회사)에 의지 하지 않아도 되는 내 능력으로 내 삶을 살고 싶다는 생각을 자주 했고, 경제적으로 독립한 전문가(장인)가 되고 싶었습니다. 

군대 후배의 추천으로 법무사에 도전하게 되었고, 쿠팡 퇴사 후 2021년 8월 말부터 법무사 1차 공부를 시작해서, 1년 만에 집에서 인강으로 22년 법무사 1차 시험에 합격하였고, 당해 2차 시험은 130명 안에 들지 못했습니다. 23년에 2차 공부를 후회없이 하였지만 불합격했습니다. 새로운 마음으로 재동차 도전중입니다. 같이 힘내요🔥🔥🔥

22년 11월 2차 시험이 끝나고 공부가 잘 되지 않아, 2023년 새해를 맞아 스터디윗미를 해보자는 생각을 했고, 열심히 실행하고 있습니다. 항상 시작이 가장 어려운 것 같습니다. JUST DO IT!!!그래도 해보는게 중요하다고 생각합니다.

미라클 모닝, 미라클 러닝, 공부, 독서 등 스스로 동기부여하려고 노력하고 있고, 가지고 있는 좋은 에너지들을 많은 분들과 주고 받고 싶어요! 부지러너 여러분들과 같이 2024년 목표 달성 해요! 들어와서 봐주시는 분들 정말 감사합니다!

Hello, My name is Boo Man. I'm preparing for the law certification exam for the 2023 
I do a real-time study with me live every day except for one day of the week. I want to motivate you as a friend who studies with you. Even though time is different, we have the same heart to strive for our dreams.

S14.description:
Yo time to lock in 👊

🔴Daily Stream schedule: https://tinyurl.com/AGzStudy

General FAQ
Name: Aryan
Age: 21
Nationality: Indian 
What do I study?: Psychology (Honours Year) at Monash University, Australia 
Stream turtle's name: Toro-sensei 🐢

I will sometimes read chat during the break time, but since it’s a short window - I will mostly read chat after completing all study sessions. 

Why 17/3 method ⌛ ?:

I have a bit of a back problem and not very strong study discipline - but valuing Pomodoro principles, I thought of reducing it to 17/3:

17 mins of study - just enough for me to get going and wanting to come back for another round without my mind numbing too much. 

3 mins of break - time to get those legs moving. 

25 mins of break - after a 4 hour period 

If you are struggling to get started with the longer Pomodoro Study sessions, give this one a go - maybe you can build from there as you gain more consistency. It's kinda like progressive overload in the gym but for our deprived persistent-focus brain systems. 

What do I do in my breaks?:

I avoid using my phone with messages cause it gets my dopamine system all wonky and makes it harder for me to get back to (*less stimulating*) focus work. So I just walk around aimlessly, take a dump if I have to, drink water, use my massage gun, look at the sky out the window - anything where I am not thinking too much about my work, but also not tempting me away from it.

💭Thoughts and purpose of this channel:

In today's world it's so difficult to congregate your focus for a particular work. There are distractions everywhere and it's too easy to lose your self-consciousness to these distractions. During this period of engrossment, It becomes essential for us to take back our consciousness and get out of the pool of distractions which seems pleasureful to swim in but is slowly submerging us into it. Best way to avoid these things is to be conscious and engage yourself in the activity which is actually important to you. It is the exact purpose of this channel. This channel is rooted onto the foundation of making progress and helping other to make progress. 

Personally, I get motivated by watching other people study. I've been watching these "study with me" sessions of other youtubers from long ago (until I started my own), and being honest, it helped me a lot. I am heartily thankful for those youtubers who helped me to make my study effective and I can confront that they created a positive impact in my life. Since I'm in their place right now, I can't be more happier than to be able to make the same positive impact on other people's life. There is a quotation saying "Helping others is the way we help ourselves". I feel that helping people and being able to make a positive impact in other people's life is the greatest thing a human can do. So, I think that you have understood the soul purpose of creating this channel.

⭐ !done (task) - when you finish your task.

S47.title: Study With Me Live | 通信制大学の学生さん、一緒に勉強しましょう！ 2025-03-30 04:30
S47.description:
通信制大学で勉強を頑張るあなたを応援！
This is a self-study session on YouTube Live hosted by a student of the Open University of Japan. The host understands English, so feel free to post your comment in English.

このチャンネルでは、放送大学生が勉強風景をライブ配信しています。
「放送大学生のみならず、全国の通信制大学で学ぶ皆さんのやる気を応援したい！」
そんな思いからこのチャンネルは誕生しました。
ホストは放送大学生ですが、放送大学以外の通信大学生さんも大歓迎です！！！
ライブ自習会への参加人数が増えたら、雑談ライブ配信でお互いの大学の情報交換もしてみたいです。

2021年4月以降は、
毎週日曜日の13〜15時まで
YouTube Liveにて配信（という名のオンライン自習会）を予定しています。

それ以外の曜日・時間帯はゲリラ的に配信します。
平日20〜23時の時間帯に行われることが多いです。

詳しい配信の日程は、チャンネル運営者のTwitterアカウントにてお知らせします。
https://twitter.com/asi_ouj


【ライブ配信についての留意事項】
・周囲の騒音を避けるため、途中で予告なくマイクをミュートにすることがあります。
・途中参加、途中離脱は自由です。
・配信終了の時間になったら、チャット欄でお知らせします。
・何かあればお気軽にチャット欄へコメントをお願いします！


【関連情報】

https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCd8zAzjHkIcPbnTDyn-q50w

放送大学 公式Webサイト
https://www.ouj.ac.jp/

放送大学生の有志が情報発信をしているチャンネル
俺たちホーダイズ【放送大学Youtuber】
https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCyOjIubV67fPBdADs-RPUlA


【チャンネル運営者について】
葦（あし）
https://twitter.com/asi_ouj
@asi_ouj

地方出身、東京で一人暮らしをしている放送大学生。
放送大学生、フリーランサー（音楽制作系）、IT企業のアルバイター、知人の会社で取締役員......という異色のクォーター兼業家。リスクの多い現代社会を生き抜く知恵を研究中。一つの肩書きに縛られない、収入源を一つに依存しない自由な生き方・働き方を探求中。コロナ禍が終息したら、海外ノマドワーカーとして東南アジアを拠点に生活する計画あり。

2013年03月　関東の某国立大学を卒業（国際学士）
2015年03月　東京都内の音楽系専門学校を卒業（専門は映像音楽制作）
2015年04月〜　放送大学の科目履修生として入学（音楽史、外国語などを履修）
2018年04月〜　放送大学の全科履修生として入学（社会と産業コースで法学専攻）
2020年04月〜　放送大学は休学中（コロナの影響で...）
2020年11月〜2021年6月　東京外国語大学オープンアカデミー　タイ語初級講座　受講
2021年4〜7月　東京外国語大学オープンアカデミー　フィジー語初級講座　受講

S63.description:
Hello, I don't know what to tell you. My mother's hair is gray, I still haven't found a job. It sounds a bit bad, yes, if you are reading this and if you are like me, don't know what you want. That's why I set myself a goal to try to help my family and save myself.

Xin chào, tôi không biết phải nói gì với bạn. Tóc mẹ tôi đã bạc, tôi vẫn chưa tìm được việc làm. Nghe có vẻ hơi tệ, đúng vậy, nếu bạn đang đọc những dòng này và nếu bạn giống tôi, không biết mình muốn gì. Đó là lý do tại sao tôi đặt ra cho mình một mục tiêu là cố gắng giúp đỡ gia đình và tự cứu mình.

S65.description:
Welcome to a productive study session! Join me for 10 hours of focused Pomodoro sessions (60 minutes of work + 10 minutes of break). Accompanied by calming rain sounds 🌧️ and soothing ambient vibes 🌿, this session is designed to help you stay concentrated and relaxed. Whether you're studying, working, or reading, let’s stay productive together!

📌 Features:

Pomodoro Timer: 60/10 work-break cycle for optimal productivity.

Relaxing Rain Ambience: Gentle rain and nature sounds for a peaceful atmosphere.

 Visual Setup: A simple desk view featuring my Lenovo X1 Carbon laptop and Honor Pad 8


✨ Tips for a Productive Session:

1. Grab your study materials, notebook, or laptop.


2. Stay hydrated and take mindful breaks during the 10-minute intervals.


3. Set your goals for each session and watch your productivity soar!



Let’s conquer our to-do lists together. Hit play and focus with me! 💻📚
